The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, specifically the Grid-Minor Theorem and its applications. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with graph minors and their properties. 

cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for finding grid minors in graphs. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper deals with algorithms and their running time. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph theory and its applications. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of finding grid minors in graphs.
